"Here is a medium-level Python coding problem for you, presented in the format that you specified:\n```json\n{\n    \"title\": \"Number Reverser (Medium)\",\n    \"description\": \"Given a positive integer, write a function `reverse_number` to reverse its digits. Do not use any string manipulation or loops. The input will always be a positive integer.\\n\\n#### Function Signature:\\n```python\\ndef reverse_number(num: int) -> int:\\n```\\n\\n#### Input:\\n- `num` (int): A positive integer\\n\\n#### Output:\\n- Returns an integer with the digits of the input number reversed.\\n\",\n    \"code\": \"def reverse_number(num: int) -> int:\\n    # Initialize a variable to store the reversed number\\n    reversed_num = 0\\n    # While there are still digits in the original number\\n    while num > 0:\\n        # Get the last digit of the number and add it to the reversed number\\n        reversed_num = reversed_num * 10 + num % 10\\n        # Remove the last digit from the original number\\n        num //= 10\\n    # Return the reversed number\\n    return reversed_num\\n\",\n    \"tests\": [\n        \"assert reverse_number(123) == 321\",\n        \"assert reverse_number(4567) == 7654\",\n        \"assert reverse_number(109) == 901\",\n        \"assert reverse_number(1203) == 3021\"\n    ]\n}\n```"